comments.author: Hardev Singh

comments.text:
+Hardev Singh

That is the stupidest analogy i've ever heard.  

The grass does not "know" shit.  It has no memory, no brain, no cognitive 
ability.  Grass is not people.   

there are plants that release chemical signals to other plants and those 
signals can trigger automated responses like an increase in the production 
of bitter tasting sap, or closing of flower buds, or even drawing more 
water through the roots during rain, that sort of thing.  But without a 
mechanism to trigger, there is no point in having the chemical signal..  It 
is a waste of resources the grass could put to better use.
